{"parse":{"title":"The Poetics of Space","pageid":2520475,"revid":849223688,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption style=\"font-style:italic;padding-bottom:0.2em;\">The Poetics of Space <span class=\"Z3988\" title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Poetics+of+Space&amp;rft.author=%5B%5BGaston+Bachelard%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=1958&amp;rft.pub=Presses+Universitaires+de+France&amp;rft.pages=241\"></span></caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:The_Poetics_of_Space_(French_edition).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"The Poetics of Space (French edition).jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/fa/The_Poetics_of_Space_%28French_edition%29.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"314\" data-file-width=\"200\" data-file-height=\"314\" /></a><div>Cover of the French edition</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Author</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Gaston_Bachelard\" title=\"Gaston Bachelard\">Gaston Bachelard</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Original&#160;title</th><td>\n<i>La Po\u00e9tique de l'Espace</i></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Translator</th><td>\nMaria Jolas</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Country</th><td>\nFrance</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Language</th><td>\nFrench</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Subject</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Architecture\" title=\"Architecture\">Architecture</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Publisher</th><td>\nPresses Universitaires de France</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\">Publication date</div></th><td>\n1958</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\">Published&#160;in English</div></th><td>\n1964</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Media&#160;type</th><td>\nPrint (<a href=\"/wiki/Hardcover\" title=\"Hardcover\">Hardback</a> &amp; <a href=\"/wiki/Paperback\" title=\"Paperback\">Paperback</a>)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Pages</th><td>\n241</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a></th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-8070-6439-4\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-8070-6439-4\">0-8070-6439-4</a> (English edition)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>The Poetics of Space</b></i> (<a href=\"/wiki/French_language\" title=\"French language\">French</a>: <i><span lang=\"fr\">La Po\u00e9tique de l'Espace</span></i>) is a 1958 book by <a href=\"/wiki/Gaston_Bachelard\" title=\"Gaston Bachelard\">Gaston Bachelard</a>. Bachelard applies the method of <a href=\"/wiki/Phenomenology_(architecture)\" title=\"Phenomenology (architecture)\">phenomenology</a> to <a href=\"/wiki/Architecture\" title=\"Architecture\">architecture</a> basing his analysis not on purported origins (as was the trend in <a href=\"/wiki/Age_of_Enlightenment\" title=\"Age of Enlightenment\">enlightenment</a> thinking about architecture) but on lived experience in architectural places and their contexts in nature. He focuses especially on the personal, emotional response to buildings both in life and in literary works, both in prose and in poetry. He is thus led to consider spatial types such as the attic, the cellar, drawers and the like. Bachelard implicitly urges architects to base their work on the experiences it will engender rather than on abstract rationales that may or may not affect viewers and users of architecture.\n</p>\n<style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r856303468\">.mw-parser-output .templatequote{overflow:hidden;margin:1em 0;padding:0 40px}.mw-parser-output .templatequote .templatequotecite{line-height:1.5em;text-align:left;padding-left:1.6em;margin-top:0}</style><blockquote class=\"templatequote\"><p>Sometimes the house of the future is better built, lighter and larger than all the houses of the past, so that the image of the dream house is opposed to that of the childhood home\u2026. Maybe it is a good thing for us to keep a few dreams of a house that we shall live in later, always later, so much later, in fact, that we shall not have time to achieve it. For a house that was final, one that stood in symmetrical relation to the house we were born in, would lead to thoughts\u2014serious, sad thoughts\u2014and not to dreams. It is better to live in a state of impermanence than in one of finality.</p><div class=\"templatequotecite\">\u2014&#8201;<cite><a href=\"/wiki/Gaston_Bachelard\" title=\"Gaston Bachelard\">Gaston Bachelard</a>, <i>The Poetics of Space</i></cite></div>\n</blockquote><p>Chapter 2: House and Universe: section VIII\n</p><h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Reception\">Reception</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Poetics_of_Space&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Reception\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><a href=\"/wiki/Camille_Paglia\" title=\"Camille Paglia\">Camille Paglia</a> has listed <i>The Poetics of Space</i> as an influence on her 1990 work of literary criticism <i><a href=\"/wiki/Sexual_Personae\" title=\"Sexual Personae\">Sexual Personae</a></i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Edward S. Casey has noted the importance of <i>The Poetics of Space</i> in and for his book <i>Getting Back into Space</i> (2009).\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Review\">Review</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Poetics_of_Space&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Review\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Joan Ockman. Harvard Design Magazine <i>Representations/Misrepresentations</i> Number 6. Fall 1998. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"http://www.harvarddesignmagazine.org/issues/6/the-poetics-of-space-by-gaston-bachelard\">[1]</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Poetics_of_Space&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Paglia, Camille (1993). <i>Sex, Art, and American Culture: Essays</i>. London: Penguin Books. p.&#160;114. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-14-017209-2\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-14-017209-2\">0-14-017209-2</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Sex%2C+Art%2C+and+American+Culture%3A+Essays&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pages=114&amp;rft.pub=Penguin+Books&amp;rft.date=1993&amp;rft.isbn=0-14-017209-2&amp;rft.au=Paglia%2C+Camille&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Poetics+of+Space\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Architecture_see_also.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/94/Architecture_see_also.svg/30px-Architecture_see_also.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"32\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/94/Architecture_see_also.svg/45px-Ar